===Supporting Cage in Harlem===
====Cage's Fame====
{{Quote|I'm your backup, not just your woman. You don't leave me behind, especially when you're gonna do something stupid.|Claire Temple to Luke Cage|Soul Brother 1}}
[[Luke Cage]] went back to work and stopped many heroin operations in the city. One night at dinner, the two talked about his operations and Temple talked about his name and brand. He was worried about money and Temple escalated that worry by asking about funds to get out of her mother's apartment. They went back to their apartment and danced before having sex.

The next morning, Temple woke up to sirens and told Cage that nor every one was for him. Cage kissed her hand and said it was there 9 to 5 before leaving. Later, Temple followed Cage to [[Harlem's Paradise]] and took many pictures of people to help Cage. The people were possible drug dealers. Cage grew worried that she was doing that. After a brief discussion about their worries for each other, they kissed. The next day, Temple was napping by Cage's side and wearing his sweatshirt. Cage got a call from [[Sugar]] giving him a tip on a location of [[Arturo Rey III]]. Cage got his sweatshirt from her and left.{{Ref|LC201}}

====Cage's Anger Problems====
Temple met up with [[Luke Cage]] at the [[Harlem Jets Practice Field]] where he set up a media day to show off his powers. Later, he told her that he was shot with a [[Judas Bullet]], but it bounced right off of him. Temple concluded that the acid bath made Cage even more indestructible. Cage then told her that his [[James Lucas|father]] came to see him. Temple told Cage to talk his troubles out with his father, but Cage refused. Temple went to [[Pop's Barber Shop]] and talked to [[Bobby Fish]]. Suddenly, she got a call from Cage and had to leave.

Meeting with Cage, Temple saw that his shoulder was dislocated from a gun shot blast. She popped the shoulder back in and told Cage that she was right about him possibly getting hurt. Cage did not want to hear it and they got into an argument. Temple told him that both [[Matt Murdock]] and him were less powerful than they thought. Cage argued he was nothing like Murdock. However, Temple said that he was and she would know. Cage then brought up [[Jessica Jones]], [[Danny Rand]], Murdock and himself, saying that she always loves people with abilities. Temple then brought up Cage's father once again causing Cage to get even angrier. He argued that his father caused [[Willis Stryker]] to turn into Diamondback, Cage to go to jail and [[Pop]]'s death. After the argument, Temple went to Lucas' church and listened to his monologue as Reverend.{{Ref|LC202}}

====Breaking Up with Cage====
{{Quote|See, um, that hole you just put in my wall - that was my childhood. That was my [[Soledad Temple|mother]] and my father, and, um... I said I would never put myself through that again. I would never live with anger again. So, um..."<br>"Look, you know... you know I would never hurt you. You know that, right?"<br>"You need to go. Right now.|Claire Temple and [[Luke Cage]]|Wig Out}}
Temple was called by [[Luke Cage]]. She arrived at a scene to find [[Cockroach Hamilton]] beaten to a pulp by Cage. This strengthened her worry of Cage's anger. She checked out Hamilton and decided to call and ambulance and [[Misty Knight]]. Later, Temple visited [[James Lucas]] to see if he truly was the monster that Cage made him out to be. After talking, she realized he was a good man. She returned to her apartment and got into another argument with Cage over his anger. She eventually told Cage that she talked to his father, causing him to lash out in anger. She suggested that he talk to Lucas, but Cage had enough. He turned around and punched the wall repeatedly. Temple took a deep breath and told him that she needed a break. She was going to visit her mother in [[Havana]]. A saddened Cage told her that he hopes they could talk the following day. He then left.{{Ref|LC203}} The next day, she left her apartment and left a note for Cage.{{Ref|LC204}}

====Caring about Luke====
While Cage resumed his vigilante activities, Temple asked [[Danny Rand]] to help him with his [[War for Harlem|war]] against Bushmaster and Cage's anger.{{Ref|LC210}} As a favor to Rand, Temple interviewed for a commercial for [[Rand Enterprises]] to showcase their cybernetic arm that they gave [[Misty Knight]].{{Ref|RCPC}}

Some time after [[Mariah Dillard]]'s death, Cage inherited the [[Harlem's Paradise]] night club. Temple attempted to speak to Cage, but is turned away, being told to return home.{{Ref|LC213}}

